// EXPECT_RUNTIME_PANIC contract requires failed in `needs_positive`: x > 0
//
// Plan 140 Ф.4 (D24 amend), acceptance F1: an UNPROVEN `requires` is checked
// at runtime in the RELEASE build (`--mode release`) and aborts fail-fast on
// violation — it is NOT silently erased.
//
// Note: this is a should-abort test. The sole assertion is EXPECT_RUNTIME_PANIC
// (nonzero exit + the structured `nova_contract_violation` message on stderr).
// We do NOT assert stdout here: `abort()` does not flush libc stdout buffers,
// so any pre-abort `println` may be lost — the abort itself is the contract.
//
// `needs_positive` carries `requires x > 0`. It is called with `-7`, which
// violates the precondition. The VerificationPipeline cannot discharge this
// precondition (it is the caller's obligation and the argument is supplied at
// the call site), so the contract stays OUT of `proven_contracts` → codegen
// emits the `nova_contract_violation(NOVA_CONTRACT_PRE, ...)` guard at the
// function-body entry. In release that guard fires → stderr message + abort()
// → nonzero exit. Before Plan 140 Ф.1 this guard was stripped in release
// (silent UB); now it stays.
//
// `UNREACHABLE` after the call is never printed because the abort terminates
// the process first.

module plan140.t1_unproven_requires_aborts

fn needs_positive(x int) -> int
    requires x > 0
=> x * 2

fn main() Io -> () {
    ro _ = needs_positive(-7)
    println("UNREACHABLE")
}
